The paper discusses the software architecture behind IBM's deep learning as a service (DLaaS), which is a platform for developers to use popular deep learning libraries in the cloud. This topic is most closely related to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG), as DLaaS is a tool for implementing deep learning models. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of GPUs and CPUs in an infrastructure as a service (IaaS) cloud, which could fall under the sub-categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning for understanding unstructured data domains such as speech and vision, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL).
